Description: Moulded ring foot and stem sherd of Attic black-glazed pottery cup-skyphos (?); fillet at junction of foot and stem; edge of foot in teo degrees, upper one slight; stem and top and inside of foot glazed; added red on fillet on stem; outer face of foot, resting surface and underside reserved, save two circles and a dot in black glaze; ligature cut on underside.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 482)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1599)
